> Wasabi may be better known as the green spicy stuff that comes with sushi, but it can be used so many other ways. Here, it's blended into a mixture of sweet soy glaze, ginger, and lime juice, creating a sauce for chicken that's equal parts tangy, aromatic, and exhilarating. The chicken is served with buttery rice and a side of roasted broccoli tossed with citrusy ponzu. Dinner winner? We think so.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel @ginger{1%thumb} and mince. Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1}.

== Ginger Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

While rice cooks, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Wasabi Soy Sauce ==

Meanwhile, in a small #bowl{}, combine scallion whites, juice from half the lime, and a pinch of salt. Set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, remaining ginger, 1/4 tsp @wasabi paste{1%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a squeeze of lime juice. Taste and add more wasabi if you like.

== Chicken ==

Pat chicken cutlets dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @chicken cutlets{10%oz} and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Add sweet soy mixture and simmer until thickened, turning chicken to coat, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

> TIP: If sauce begins to thicken too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Toss broccoli with @ponzu sauce{6%ml}.

Divide rice, broccoli, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with any remaining sauce from pan and pickled scallion whites (draining first). Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.